 France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Vergy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Herefordshire): nickname from Middle English <i>verrei</i>, <i>verie</i> ‘true; reliable, trustworthy’ (Old French <i>verai</i>).","Irish: variant of <b>McVerry</b>, a shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fearadhaigh</b>, itself an unlenited and subsequently voiced variant of <b>Mac Fhearadhaigh</b>, ‘son of <i>Fearadhach</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘manly’. Compare   McAree   and   McCary  ; also the surnames   Ferry   and   Farry  , from <i>Ó Fearadhaigh</i>.","History: The widow Bridget Very settled with her children in Salem, MA, <i>c.</i> 1634. She had many prominent descendants, including the poet Jones Very (1813–1880)."],"variants":[{"name":"McAree","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fhearadhaigh</b> ‘son of <i>Fearadhach</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘manly’ (from <i>fear</i> ‘man’). Pronunciation of this name as <i>McAree</i> led to misinterpretation as <i>Mac an Rí</i> ‘son of the king’ and thus to ‘translation’ as   King  . See   McGarry  ."]}]},{"name":"Aluis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["= Latin <i>Aloysius</i>, probably from Germanic <i>Alwisi</i> ‘all wise’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aluis de Vergy was born about 1213, in Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France, her father, Hugues de Vergy II, was 29 and her mother, Elisabeth de Nully, was 25. She married Jean de Til-Châtel about 1240. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France."},"et":{"Abt 1213–":"umbes 1213–Surnud","1213–Female":"1213–Surnud","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1240–1300":"1240–1300","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1275":"1275","1185":"1185","1240":"1240","Abt 1213":"umbes 1213","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1213–":"noin 1213–Kuollut","1213–Female":"1213–Kuollut","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1240–1300":"1240–1300","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1275":"1275","1185":"1185","1240":"1240","Abt 1213":"noin 1213","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Ranska","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1213–":"environ 1213–Décédée","1213–Female":"1213–Décédée","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1240–1300":"1240–1300","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1190":"1190","Abt 1240":"environ 1240","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1275":"1275","1185":"1185","1240":"1240","Abt 1213":"environ 1213","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bou